3. Presentation
Each student presents their own research ideas at least once per semester. All students are expected to be helpful members of the seminar team by improving the research work shared with them. When students present their own research as the basis for doing philosophy socially in the seminar, they will have 3 choices: 
* to hold a 40-minute presentation followed by a critical and constructive effort to improve the work by the whole seminar; 
* to submit a paper (maximum 20 pages) to be pre-read before the seminar. The seminar will then consist of critical and constructive efforts to improve the work by the whole seminar; 
* to produce a 3-page version of their research work, which will be read for 40 minutes in the seminar and followed by critical and constructive efforts to improve the work by the whole seminar.
